\f0\b\fs32 \cf3 How to run\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Source ROS and the workspace:\

\f2\b0 source /opt/ros/jazzy/setup.bash\uc0\u8232 source /home/ws/install/setup.bash
\f0\b\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Terminal 1:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf0 ros2 launch zed_wrapper zed_camera.launch.py\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 -> publishes raw point cloud from the ZED camera
\f1\i0 \

\f0\b Terminal 2:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf0 ros2 run rover_perception cloud_to_target_frame --ros-arg -r /point_cloud/cloud_registered:=/zed/zed_node/point_cloud/cloud_registered\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 -> transforms the point cloud into the target frame
\f1\i0 \

\f0\b Terminal 3:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf0 ros2 run rover_perception height_costmap\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 -> publishes occupancy grid 
\f1\i0 \

\f0\b Terminal 4:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf0 ros2 run rover_scp map_publisher_node --ros-args -p start_x:=10 -p start_y:=10 -p end_x:=90 -p end_y:=90\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 -> publishes map metadata and SDF grid 
\f1\i0 \

\f0\b Terminal 5:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa180\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf0 ros2 run rover_scp rover_pp_node\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 -> C++ planning node that runs SCP and publishes trajectory-generated control commands to the rover on /cmd_vel}